With Florida under a lockdown due to the coronavirus pandemic, there’s one business deemed essential by Florida’s governor that is raising some eyebrows: pro wrestling.
The WWE Performance Center is located in metro Orlando so chairman and CEO Vince McMahon is able to continue putting on his show — without fans.
“With some conversation with the governor’s office, regarding the governor’s order, they were deemed an essential business.
The WWE Performance Center is a finishing school of sorts for wrestlers.
Vince McMahon, and his wife, Linda, have deep connections to President Donald Trump, whose support last year launched DeSantis into the Florida Governor’s Mansion.